+  status: BACKLOG
+  section: 10. Operational and workflow requirements
+  requirement: 'A local (non-CI) run of `tests/integration/test_state_git_backend_live.py` MUST NOT be able to hang silently
+    and indefinitely on an unconfigured `git push` credential -- it should fail fast with a clear error, or the prerequisite
+    should be documented/scripted so it''s never hit blind. Found live, 2026-07-19: `git push` to `origin` blocked ~35 minutes
+    with zero output (no credential prompt text, no error) because `GH_TOKEN` being present in the environment does not by
+    itself wire git''s push auth -- neither `run_git()`''s 120s subprocess timeout nor pytest catches this, since the hang
+    is inside git''s own credential-resolution step. Root-caused and worked around this session (temporary `http.https://github.com/.extraheader`
+    from `GH_TOKEN`, removed after) -- documented as a prerequisite in the test file''s own docstring; not yet a scripted/automatic
+    fix. **Second, distinct variant found 2026-07-22**: a plain `git push origin main` (outside `run_git()`, invoked directly)
+    hung identically -- root cause this time was Windows'' `git-credential-manager.exe` invoked as an interactive helper,
+    confirmed alive as a detached process (`tasklist`) even after the parent `git push` was killed by this session''s own
+    2-minute shell timeout. `_git.py`''s new `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0` default (added this session for `run_git()`''s own ~20
+    internal call sites) does NOT cover this case -- it only applies inside `run_git()`, never to an ad-hoc shell `git` invocation
+    outside it. Worked around by killing the orphaned helper process and retrying with `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=0` plus `-c credential.helper="!gh
+    auth git-credential"` set explicitly for that one command. **Third variant, 2026-07-22, a wrong-format auth header rather
+    than a hang**: `gitsafety/clone.py::push_branch()`''s first version sent `http.extraheader="AUTHORIZATION: bearer {token}"`
+    -- authenticates fine against GitHub''s REST API (`github_api/client.py`''s own `_headers()`) but NOT against GitHub''s
+    git-http backend, which silently falls through to normal credential-helper resolution instead of failing on the header
+    itself, then hits this row''s own already-documented `GCM_INTERACTIVE=never` fail-fast path. Found live (a real `open_presentation_pr`
+    dispatch against `aspose-cells-foss/Aspose.Cells-FOSS-for-Java`), fixed by switching to Basic auth (`x-access-token:{token}`,
+    base64-encoded) -- matching this row''s own already-documented working precedent exactly (`AUTH=$(printf ''x-access-token:%s''
+    "$GH_TOKEN" \'
+  acceptance_evidence: 'base64 -w0); ... "AUTHORIZATION: basic $AUTH"`), which a careful re-read at the time of the bug would
+    have caught. No unit test can catch this specific class (a local file-transport remote makes any header value a no-op)
+    -- only a real HTTPS push proves the format.'
+  traceability_raw: 'No fix designed yet -- candidates: a `conftest.py` fixture that configures/tears down the extraheader
+    automatically for `@pytest.mark.live` git tests, or a fast preflight check that fails clearly (e.g. `git ls-remote` against
+    a scratch ref) before the real test body attempts a push. **Fourth variant, 2026-07-23 (Wave 14.2 live proof)**: `state/git_backend.py`''s
+    own durable-state run-lock push (`refs/readme-agent-state/run-locks/...`, THIS project''s own remote, not a target pilot
+    repo) hit the identical root cause -- `GH_TOKEN` present in the environment but never wired to this repo''s own local
+    git push auth. Two different symptoms from the same cause, both observed in the same live run: the first attempt (`cells/java`)
+    hung silently for over 90 minutes (`git-credential-manager` invoked as an interactive helper, exactly the second documented
+    variant above, confirmed via `Get-Process` showing 195s of accumulated CPU time with zero progress); the second attempt
+    (`.NET`), after the hung process was killed, failed fast and cleanly instead (`fatal: Cannot prompt because user interactivity
+    has been disabled... could not read Username for ''https://github.com''`, exit code 3) -- the same missing-auth root cause
+    hit `GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT`''s fail-fast path instead of the interactive-helper hang path, non-deterministically depending
+    on some difference between the two invocations not yet isolated. Fixed for this session by applying this row''s own already-documented
+    working precedent directly to this repo''s local git config: `git config --local http.https://github.com/.extraheader
+    "AUTHORIZATION: basic $(printf ''x-access-token:%s'' "$GH_TOKEN" \| base64 -w0)"` -- verified with a real scratch push+delete
+    to `refs/readme-agent-state/_auth_test_2026_07_23` before retrying the live proof. This is a session-local git-config
+    fix, not a code change -- a real GitHub Actions runner has its own, already-working credential wiring (`GITHUB_TOKEN`
+    auto-injected by `actions/checkout`), so this specific gap is local-development-environment-only, but the underlying "GH_TOKEN
+    alone doesn''t wire push auth" lesson is the same one this row has now recorded four separate times. | Found during 2026-07-19
+    specialist-domain-isolation live-verification pass; no owning wave -- logged per Decision 29 so it isn''t silently lost'
+  decision_refs:
+  - '29'
